    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n97" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγλαός</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γαλ-</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">splendid, shining,
            bright;</span> epith. of pellucid water, golden gifts, etc.; met.
          ‘illustrious,’ ‘famous,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">υἱός</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.188</span></i>; ‘stately,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 19.385</span></i>; in reproach <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέραι ἀγλαέ</span>, ‘brilliant with the bow,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 11.385</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
